We recommended that Management:

Direct the Municipal Budget Officer to exclude the income from operation of Libon Community College from locally sourced income, instead, it should be part of income from external sources; 

Require the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Treasurer to reconcile the total budgeted amount and actual receipts presented in the SCBAA and SRS;

Require the Municipal Budget Officer and Municipal Treasurer to carefully review and assess their revenue projections for each income account to ensure systematic and realistic forecasting of revenue collections for the ensuing year; and

Thereafter, require the Municipal Treasurer to conduct periodic review and take the necessary actions to ensure collection targets are attained.

We recommended that Management:

Provide for the payment of Subsistence Allowance of MSWDO Personnel in compliance with “Magna Carta for Public Social Workers”;

Require the Municipal Health Office personnel to refund the excess payment of subsistence allowances amounting to ₱121,729.29.

We recommended that the local government unit establish or formulate specific guidelines in the granting of all kinds of financial assistance to its constituents to ensure an efficient implementation of the program and economical utilization of its limited resources. The guidelines may include, among others, the following:

Qualifications of the recipients, to include income levels which may be determined by the screening committee for all kinds of financial assistance;

For medical assistance,-Categorize ailments, such as ordinary, medical or surgical; 

Maximum and reasonable amount of financial assistance for each category;

Frequency or maximum number of entitlements in a year;

Mode of payment;

Uniform authorization and documentary requirement such as certificate from the barangay, income levels, social worker case study, official receipts, hospital bills and other basic requirements to establish validity and correctness of the claims.

